# Downloaded CC0 GLB asset packs — reproduced by `npm run fetch:assets`, not
# committed (tens–hundreds of MB of binaries). The generated manifest IS committed
# so the game knows its catalog even before assets are fetched. The seed-set
# sidecar overrides under public/models are kept. See scripts/fetch-assets.mjs.
public/models/**/*.glb
public/models/**/*.gltf
public/models/**/*.bin
public/models/**/*.png
public/models/**/*.jpg

# Decimated Vita robot meshes — reproduced by `npm run prep:robot` from the
# read-only sim-app robot bundle (39 MB raw → ~3 MB decimated). Not committed
# (binary STL blobs). The committed manifest.json + vita01evt.xml + keyframes.xml
# + walk.json describe the robot + its motion so the game knows its rig even
# before the meshes are prepped. See scripts/prep-robot.mjs.
public/robots/**/meshes/*.STL
public/robots/**/meshes/*.stl
